p: Most samples were positive for chikungunya and Sindbis (73.1% and 19.4%, respectively). Out of the 73 arboviruses-positive samples, 49 were positive for chikungunya (29 males and 20 females). In contrast to this, other arboviruses were circulating in low rate such as RVFV (7.4%). Results also revealed that both SINV and malaria parasite shared the same positive proportions among the detected samples (10.9%) with significant differences ( P ˂ 0.05).
